In chrome and safari, the ```console.log``` was triggered in different order. [Example](https://codesandbox.io/s/amazing-payne-4lmxo) will show different result if opened in different browsers.

React version: 16.13.1

## Steps To Reproduce

1. Run following code in chrome and safari.
2. Check console log

```jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";

const Test = props => {
  useEffect(() => {
    console.log("useEffect in child");
  }, []);

  return "Test useEffect";
};

const App = () => {
  setTimeout(() => {
    console.log("timeout in render");
  }, 0);

  return <Test />;
};

export default App
```

Link to code example:

[Example](https://codesandbox.io/s/amazing-payne-4lmxo)

